oups, efforts to escape to the forests, and Jewish participation in the Soviet partisan movement. Bauer’s book is a definitive examination of the demise of the shtetls, a topic of vast importance to the history of the Holocaust.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)zPoland. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)zSoviet Union. 0aShtetls. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Eastern.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030015209840uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030015488740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300154887423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300154887/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY